# Secret-safe + lean build context for the P1a reproducible adapter image.
# Copied into the build context root as `.dockerignore` by repro-build-test.sh.
#
# The context is already a `git archive <SHA>` (tracked files only -> no .git, no
# untracked creds), but this is defense-in-depth per scion-avoid[10] / the cred-free
# pillar-2 acceptance line: NOTHING secret rides into a layer, even if the Dockerfile
# COPYs broadly.

# ── secret/cred surface (load-bearing) ──
.git
.gitignore
.ois
**/.ois
**/*.env
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*.crt
**/*secret*
**/*credential*
**/id_rsa*
**/.npmrc

# ── regenerated-at-build (must NOT ride in; tsc/npm ci recreate deterministically) ──
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/*.tgz
**/coverage
**/*.log

# ── irrelevant-to-adapter subtrees (lean context; only packages/ + adapters/ + root
#    manifests + scripts/build are needed) ──
hub
modules
deploy
docs
agents
blueprints
skills
local-state
undefined
.github
**/.terraform
